        <h3>How big is The Moon</h3>
        The moon's diameter is around  2,159.2 miles (3,475 km), making it less than a third the width of Earth. [<a href="https://www.space.com/18135-how-big-is-the-moon.html">REF</a>]
        The moon's mass is 7.35 x 10^22 kg which is 81 times smaller than the Earth. [<a href="https://www.space.com/18135-how-big-is-the-moon.html">REF</a>]
