        <h3>What is a Lunar Eclipse</h3>
        A lunar eclipse happens when the Earth gets between the Moon and the Sun which casts a shadow on the Moon. [<a href="https://spaceplace.nasa.gov/eclipses/en/">REF</a>]
        <span class="tooltipNew">
            [*]
            <span class="tooltiptextNew">
                These can include total, partial, or penumbral were the moon is in the faint shadow of The Moon called the penumbra.[<a href="https://spaceplace.nasa.gov/eclipses/en/">REF</a>]
            </span>
        </span>
        The reason we do not have monthly solar eclipses is because The Moon's movment around The Earth is tilted compared to Earth's rotation around The Sun. [<a href="https://spaceplace.nasa.gov/eclipses/en/">REF</a>]
        Below is a diagram showing how a lunar eclipse works. <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Geometry_of_a_Lunar_Eclipse.svg">source</a>
